  <text>
     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <head>Ad Gregorium</head>
   <lg>
      <l>Dulces docta modos loqui</l>
      <l>Dum Christum celebrat Calliope tua:</l>
      <l>Dum tristis querulo temporis, &amp; loci</l>
      <l>Defles carmine crimina:</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <pb facs="5"/>
      <l>Praestans dum quatitur Chelis:</l>
      <l>Dum certas fidibus non triuialibus:</l>
      <l>Dum fundis numeros nobilis (O) bonos:</l>
      <l>Vincis maxime Gregori.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Primae vos superas viros,</l>
      <l>Et Maya genitus, Linus, &amp; Orpheus,</l>
      <l>Alcaei taceat barbiton optimum:</l>
      <l>Vincis barbiton Alcaei.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Dum pascis domini gregem,</l>
      <l>(Est <gap reason="foreign">
            <desc>〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉</desc>
         </gap> tua sic cignia <gap reason="foreign">
            <desc>〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉</desc>
         </gap>)</l>
      <l>Dulcis, dulcior es mellibus Atticis:</l>
      <l>Claris clarior omnibus.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Agros flumine dum rigas:</l>
      <l>Dum cogis pecudes montibus Israel:</l>
      <l>Et dum manna fluit faucibus inclytis:</l>
      <l>Fauces mella stipant tuum.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Viuis maxime Gregori,</l>
      <l>Laetis, at{que} bonis aedite saeculis.</l>
      <l>Acris, melli fluus, doctiloquus, pius,</l>
      <l>Vincis maxime Gregori.</l>
   </lg>
</div>
